### Run auth.http's "Login" request first — it sets the shared authToken used below.

### Create an expense
# @name createExpense
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Groceries",
  "amount": 42.5,
  "currency": "USD",
  "category": "food",
  "date": "2024-01-15",
  "notes": "Weekly shop"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("expenseId", response.body.data.id);
%}

### List expenses
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get a single expense
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{expenseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Update an expense
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{expenseId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "amount": 45
}

### Delete an expense
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{expenseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
